(1.) Not their preſent eſtate towards God. For a ſore Judgment may befall a man greatly in Gods favour, for a foul Crime; as in the caſe of the Death of Davids child, inflicted, even after his Repentance, for thoſe hainous ſins of Adultery

and Murder; becauſe he had by them cauſed the Enemies of God to blaſpheme;
                     2 Sam. 12.14. doth evidently appear.
